health-insurance.heading: Health Insurance
health-insurance.contant: Health insurance, a little different than the critical illness or life insurance, is <em>a contract between the insurance company and the policy holder or insured that requires an insurance company to pay some or all bills of a person’s healthcare costs while the insured or policy holder pays the premium to the insurance provider.

super-visa-medical-insurance.heading: Super Visa Medical Insurance
super-visa-medical-insurance.contant: Super visa insurance for parents visiting their children or grand parents vesting their grand children is a requirement for parents/grandparents planning to visit their children in Canada on Super Visa basis.

super-visa-insurance.heading: Super Visa Insurance
super-visa-insurance.contant: Super visa insurance for parents and grand parents is a requirement for parents/grandparents planning to visit their children in Canada.

life-insurance.heading: Life Insurance
life-insurance.contant: Life insurance is a contract between insured and policy owner to pay an agreed upon amount of money upon death or disability of the insured person.
